Conducted variety of research projects primarily examining cultural variation in how teaching and learning arrangements are provided for Mexican- and European- heritage children in family and community settings.  Examined these themes in the context of observational studies that noted how children engaged in collaborative activities with parents and with their peers.  Supervised and informally mentored several research assistants during the course of this work.

Conceptualized, planned and moderated studies to refine client ideas and hone technology products.  Conducted UX research on a wide range of technology products from online Brain Atlas to gaming applications for mobile.
included.title: User Experience Researcher

included.description: Led research projects to generate and test design concepts for Microsoft Business Customer portal, a volume licensing platform that is responsible for $60+ billion in Microsoft sales.  Developed key scenarios and success metrics for onboarding, planning, purchasing, analytics and support.  Research resolved ongoing disagreements regarding content and direction, and helped to course-correct business strategy.  Also developed and implemented research programs in the fast changing B2B environment of MSFT Business Partners and their Small to Medium Business Customers.
included.title: Senior User Experience Researcher

included.description: Conducted UX Research, primarily in the form of interviews (stakeholders and users) and informal usability testing, to inform redesign of an e-commerce and university website.  Worked with Senior Designers to build and refine UX Design skills including development of IA maps, visual mock-ups, user-flows and wireframes.
